This notebook contains chunks of R script computing indices for five
different behaviours:

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  Travelled distance
\item
  Tendency to spend time at the top of the pond
\item
  Latency to cross an exploration box
\item
  Tendency to hide
\item
  Shoaling tendency
\end{itemize}

There is no behavioural test for the last index, but the metric is
retrieved from the data collected for the four other tests. This
notebook is so far built to compute the indices for one week of
treatment, from the four weekly datasets.

I create the \textbf{clean.data} \emph{function} to clean my data. This
function does the following:

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  It subsets a few columns of interest from the raw data (i.e.~time,
  antenna, id)
\item
  It keeps only one read per individual and per second for a given
  antenna (i.e.~remove repeats)
\item
  I assign every individual to a category named \emph{time of the day},
  indicating if it was tested during the morning or during the
  afternoon.
\item
  It renames the antenna as \emph{1, 2, 3 and 4} (see Fig 1 \& Fig 2).
\item
  It removes the ghost reads, and the reads coming from antenna tests,
  to only keep the fish reads in the ponds.
\item
  It assigns each individual to its \emph{pond number} and
  \emph{treatment sequence}.
\end{itemize}

\hypertarget{antenna-changes}{%
\subsubsection{2.2 Antenna changes}\label{antenna-changes}}

Next, I want to keep the reads corresponding to antenna changes. For
each individual, if an invidiual has been read at the antenna the
following way - 1, 1, 1, 2, 2, 3 -, we only keep the first reads for
each sequence at the same antenna. The output is, for the example above:
1, 2, 3.

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
  \CommentTok{\# I define my objects}
\NormalTok{    df\_list\_red }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{list}\NormalTok{()}
\NormalTok{    nb\_ind }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{length}\NormalTok{(EB\_list\_df\_id) }\CommentTok{\# number of individuals that have been read by the antennas}

    
    
  \CommentTok{\# For each individual, I want to obtain the reads corresponding to an antenna change and the}
  \CommentTok{\# corresponding antenna number, time and fish id.}
    \ControlFlowTok{for}\NormalTok{ (i }\ControlFlowTok{in} \DecValTok{1}\SpecialCharTok{:}\NormalTok{nb\_ind) \{}
\NormalTok{      EB\_list\_df\_id[[i]] }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ EB\_list\_df\_id[[i]][}\FunctionTok{order}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{as.POSIXct}\NormalTok{(EB\_list\_df\_id[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{time)),]}
\NormalTok{      changes          }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{which}\NormalTok{(EB\_list\_df\_id[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna}\SpecialCharTok{!=} \FunctionTok{lag}\NormalTok{(EB\_list\_df\_id[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna))}
\NormalTok{      antenna          }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(EB\_list\_df\_id[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{], EB\_list\_df\_id[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna[changes])}
\NormalTok{      time             }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(EB\_list\_df\_id[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{time[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{], EB\_list\_df\_id[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{time[changes])}
\NormalTok{      id               }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(EB\_list\_df\_id[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{id[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{], EB\_list\_df\_id[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{id[changes])}
\NormalTok{      df\_list\_red[[i]] }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{data.frame}\NormalTok{(antenna, time, id)}
\NormalTok{    \}}

    
    
  \CommentTok{\# I bind the rows of the list (i.e. make it a dataframe, as it initially was)}
\NormalTok{    EB\_Changes }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{bind\_rows}\NormalTok{(df\_list\_red)}
\NormalTok{    EB\_Changes }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{as.data.frame}\NormalTok{(EB\_Changes)}
\NormalTok{    EB\_Changes }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{merge}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{unique}\NormalTok{(EB\_clean\_df[}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{,}\DecValTok{4}\NormalTok{,}\DecValTok{5}\NormalTok{,}\DecValTok{6}\NormalTok{)]), EB\_Changes, }\AttributeTok{by =} \StringTok{"id"}\NormalTok{, }\AttributeTok{all =} \ConstantTok{FALSE}\NormalTok{)}

  \CommentTok{\# EB\_Changes is basically the initial \textquotesingle{}df\textquotesingle{} but the repeated reads}
  \CommentTok{\# have been eliminated only to keep the first one.}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

\hypertarget{latency-to-cross-the-box}{%
\subsubsection{2.3 Latency to cross the
box}\label{latency-to-cross-the-box}}

I build a function which has, as:

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  Input = A data frame containing the antenna change reads for one
  individual
\item
  Output = The first full cross of the exploration box, or an empty
  dataframe if the individual hasn't fully crossed the box.
\end{itemize}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{first.cross }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \ControlFlowTok{function}\NormalTok{(df)\{}
  
  \CommentTok{\# I identify all the row numbers at which the individual started the sequential}
  \CommentTok{\# crossing between antenna 1 and antenna 4}
\NormalTok{  rowstarts\_1234  }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{unlist}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{gregexpr}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"1234"}\NormalTok{, }\FunctionTok{paste}\NormalTok{(df}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna, }\AttributeTok{collapse=}\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{)))}
  
  
  
  \CommentTok{\# If the individual has crossed the box from antenna 1 to antenna 4.}
  \ControlFlowTok{if}\NormalTok{ (rowstarts\_1234[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{] }\SpecialCharTok{!=} \SpecialCharTok{{-}}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{)\{}
  
  \CommentTok{\# Then, I subset the first full box cross (1,2,3,4)}
\NormalTok{    first\_cross\_1234 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ df[}\FunctionTok{sort}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{outer}\NormalTok{(rowstarts\_1234[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{], (}\DecValTok{0}\SpecialCharTok{:}\DecValTok{3}\NormalTok{), }\StringTok{"+"}\NormalTok{))), ]}
\NormalTok{    first\_cross\_1234 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ first\_cross\_1234 }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%} \FunctionTok{spread}\NormalTok{(antenna,time)}
\NormalTok{    first\_cross\_1234 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{as.data.frame}\NormalTok{(first\_cross\_1234)}
    \FunctionTok{names}\NormalTok{(first\_cross\_1234) }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"id"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"time\_of\_day"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Pond"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Treatment\_seq"}\NormalTok{, }
                                 \StringTok{"Ant1"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Ant2"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Ant3"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Ant4"}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{    \}}
  
  
  
  \CommentTok{\# On the other hand, if the individual has crossed the box from antenna 1 to antenna 4.}
  \ControlFlowTok{if}\NormalTok{ (rowstarts\_1234[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{] }\SpecialCharTok{==} \SpecialCharTok{{-}}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{)\{first\_cross\_1234 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} 
  \CommentTok{\# Then I just obtain an empty tibble.  }
\NormalTok{    first\_cross\_4321 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} 
    \FunctionTok{tibble}\NormalTok{( )\}}
 
  
  
  \CommentTok{\# Same as above but between antenna 4 and antenna 1. }
\NormalTok{    rowstarts\_4321  }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{unlist}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{gregexpr}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"4321"}\NormalTok{, }\FunctionTok{paste}\NormalTok{(df}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna, }\AttributeTok{collapse=}\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{)))}
  \ControlFlowTok{if}\NormalTok{ (rowstarts\_4321[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{] }\SpecialCharTok{!=} \SpecialCharTok{{-}}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{)\{}
\NormalTok{  first\_cross\_4321 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ df[}\FunctionTok{sort}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{outer}\NormalTok{(rowstarts\_4321[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{], (}\DecValTok{0}\SpecialCharTok{:}\DecValTok{3}\NormalTok{), }\StringTok{"+"}\NormalTok{))), ]}
\NormalTok{  first\_cross\_4321 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ first\_cross\_4321 }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%} \FunctionTok{spread}\NormalTok{(antenna,time)}
\NormalTok{  first\_cross\_4321 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{as.data.frame}\NormalTok{(first\_cross\_4321)}
  
  
  \FunctionTok{names}\NormalTok{(first\_cross\_4321) }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"id"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"time\_of\_day"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Pond"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Treatment\_seq"}\NormalTok{, }
                               \StringTok{"Ant1"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Ant2"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Ant3"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Ant4"}\NormalTok{)\}}
  \ControlFlowTok{if}\NormalTok{ (rowstarts\_4321[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{] }\SpecialCharTok{==} \SpecialCharTok{{-}}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{)\{first\_cross\_4321 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} 
    \FunctionTok{tibble}\NormalTok{( )\}}
  
    
  \CommentTok{\# I rbind my two tibbles.}
\NormalTok{  first\_cross }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{rbind}\NormalTok{(first\_cross\_1234, first\_cross\_4321)}
  
  
  
  
  \CommentTok{\# If the individual did at least one full cross...}
  \ControlFlowTok{if}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{dim}\NormalTok{(first\_cross)[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{] }\SpecialCharTok{!=} \DecValTok{0}\NormalTok{)\{}
  \CommentTok{\# Then, I subset its first full cross.}
\NormalTok{    first\_cross }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ first\_cross[}\FunctionTok{order}\NormalTok{(first\_cross}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{Ant2),]}
\NormalTok{    first\_cross }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ first\_cross[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{,]\}}
  
  
  \CommentTok{\# On the other hand, if the individual hasn\textquotesingle{}t fully crossed the box...}
  \ControlFlowTok{if}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{dim}\NormalTok{(first\_cross)[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{] }\SpecialCharTok{==} \DecValTok{0}\NormalTok{)\{}
  \CommentTok{\# Then, I just obtain a data frame with NAs.}
\NormalTok{      first\_cross }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{data.frame}\NormalTok{(}\AttributeTok{id =}\NormalTok{ df}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{id[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{], }\AttributeTok{Ant1 =} \ConstantTok{NA}\NormalTok{,}
                   \AttributeTok{Ant2 =} \ConstantTok{NA}\NormalTok{, }\AttributeTok{Ant3 =} \ConstantTok{NA}\NormalTok{, }\AttributeTok{Ant4 =} \ConstantTok{NA}\NormalTok{)\}}
  
    
  \FunctionTok{return}\NormalTok{(first\_cross)\} }\CommentTok{\# end of the function}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

Next, I can apply the function above to all individuals. I then add a
column containing the latency to fully explore the box.

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\CommentTok{\# I split my data frame per individual}
\NormalTok{  EB\_changes\_list }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{split}\NormalTok{(EB\_Changes, }\AttributeTok{f =}\NormalTok{ EB\_Changes}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{id)}


\CommentTok{\# I define a list}
\NormalTok{  first\_crosses }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{list}\NormalTok{()}

  
\CommentTok{\# For each individual...}
  \ControlFlowTok{for}\NormalTok{(i }\ControlFlowTok{in} \DecValTok{1}\SpecialCharTok{:}\FunctionTok{length}\NormalTok{(EB\_changes\_list))\{}
    \CommentTok{\# I want to obtain the first full cross of the box, using the function defined above.}
\NormalTok{    first\_crosses[[i]] }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{first.cross}\NormalTok{(EB\_changes\_list[[i]])}
\NormalTok{  \}}
  
  
\CommentTok{\# I bind the dataframes of my list together to obtain a dataframe containing}
\CommentTok{\# The first cross of all individuals that crossed the box.}
\NormalTok{  EB\_Lat }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{bind\_rows}\NormalTok{(first\_crosses)}


  
\CommentTok{\# I add a new column with the time to cross the box since the start of the test}
\CommentTok{\# For the morning}
\NormalTok{  EB\_Lat\_morning }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{mutate}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{subset}\NormalTok{(EB\_Lat, time\_of\_day }\SpecialCharTok{==} \StringTok{"Morning"}\NormalTok{), }
                           \AttributeTok{time\_since\_start =} \FunctionTok{difftime}\NormalTok{(Ant2, start\_morning, }\AttributeTok{units=}\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}m\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{))}
\CommentTok{\# For the afternoon}
\NormalTok{  EB\_Lat\_afternoon }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{mutate}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{subset}\NormalTok{(EB\_Lat, time\_of\_day }\SpecialCharTok{==} \StringTok{"Afternoon"}\NormalTok{), }
                             \AttributeTok{time\_since\_start =} \FunctionTok{difftime}\NormalTok{(Ant2, start\_afternoon, }\AttributeTok{units=}\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}m\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{))}

  
\CommentTok{\# I bind the two, and transform my column (in minutes) as numerical}
\NormalTok{  EB\_Lat }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{rbind}\NormalTok{(EB\_Lat\_morning, EB\_Lat\_afternoon)}
\NormalTok{  EB\_Lat}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{time\_since\_start }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{as.numeric}\NormalTok{(EB\_Lat}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{time\_since\_start)}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

I make a small function, to modify my data frame containing the crossing
sequence of all individuals that crossed the box in a way that I have a
data set handy for plotting. In this function, I add the individuals
variables (i.e.~pond, Time of the day, treatment sequence, hereafter
\emph{variables}). Finally, I give the maximal value (that is, 150
minutes) to all individuals that never crossed the box.

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{finalise.EB }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \ControlFlowTok{function}\NormalTok{(EB\_Lat, EB\_variables) \{}
\CommentTok{\# I add the environemntal variables}
\NormalTok{  EB\_Lat\_final }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{merge}\NormalTok{(EB\_Lat[}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"id"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"time\_since\_start"}\NormalTok{)], }
\NormalTok{                        EB\_variables[}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}id\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"time\_of\_day"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Pond"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Treatment\_seq"}\NormalTok{)], }
                        \AttributeTok{by =} \StringTok{\textquotesingle{}id\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{, }\AttributeTok{all =}\NormalTok{ T)}

  
  
\CommentTok{\# I assign the maximal values to all the fish that never crossed the box.}
\NormalTok{  EB\_Lat\_final}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{time\_since\_start[}\FunctionTok{is.na}\NormalTok{(EB\_Lat\_final}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{time\_since\_start)] }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \DecValTok{150}

  
  
\CommentTok{\# I create an exploration index, for which a low value means that individuals never }
\CommentTok{\# explored the box, and a high value means that individuals explored it early.}
\NormalTok{  EB\_Lat\_final}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{Expl\_index }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}  \FunctionTok{abs}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(EB\_Lat\_final}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{time\_since\_start }\SpecialCharTok{{-}} \DecValTok{150}\NormalTok{))}

  
  
\CommentTok{\# I only keep the variables of interest for plotting.}
\NormalTok{  EB\_Lat\_final }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ EB\_Lat\_final[}\FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"id"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Pond"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Treatment\_seq"}\NormalTok{, }
                                 \StringTok{"time\_since\_start"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"time\_of\_day"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Expl\_index"}\NormalTok{)]}
  
  \FunctionTok{return}\NormalTok{(EB\_Lat\_final)\}}


\CommentTok{\# I run the function}
\NormalTok{  EB\_Lat\_final }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{finalise.EB}\NormalTok{(EB\_Lat, EB\_variables)}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

I use the finalise.EB function to clean up the output and to obtain a
plottable dataframe.

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\CommentTok{\# I run the finalise. EB function defined above to clean my output}
\NormalTok{  EB\_Lat\_final }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{finalise.EB}\NormalTok{(EB\_Lat, EB\_variables)}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

\hypertarget{function-computing-the-travelled-distance-per-individual}{%
\subsubsection{3.2 Function computing the travelled distance per
individual}\label{function-computing-the-travelled-distance-per-individual}}

First, I remove repeated reads at a single antenna, and obtain the
antenna changes. In other words, for each individual, I reduce the
sequence of reads (e.g., reads at antennas 1, 1, 1, 2, 2, 3) in a way
that I only keep one read in a repeated sequence at the same antenna
(e.g., reads at antennas 1, 2, 3).

Second, I compute the travelled distance between these antennas, for
every change, and sum them up. At the end, I will obtain the minimal
total distance that a fish has travelled between the antennas during
2:30 hours.

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{    trav.dist }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \ControlFlowTok{function}\NormalTok{(new\_dataset)\{}
    
    \CommentTok{\# I split my dataframe into a list of dataframes (one object per individual)}
\NormalTok{    df\_list }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{split}\NormalTok{(new\_dataset, }\AttributeTok{f =}\NormalTok{ new\_dataset}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{id)}



\DocumentationTok{\#\#  1. REMOVE THE REPEATED READS AND OBTAIN THE ANTENNA CHANGE}

    \CommentTok{\# I define \textquotesingle{}df\_list\_red\textquotesingle{} which is basically \textquotesingle{}df\_list\textquotesingle{} except that the input vector}
    \CommentTok{\# is replaced by the output vector.}
\NormalTok{    df\_list\_red }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{list}\NormalTok{()}
\NormalTok{    nb\_ind }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{length}\NormalTok{(df\_list)}

    
    \CommentTok{\# I obtain the output vectors and the associated time and Identifier}
    \ControlFlowTok{for}\NormalTok{ (i }\ControlFlowTok{in} \DecValTok{1}\SpecialCharTok{:}\NormalTok{nb\_ind) \{}
\NormalTok{      changes          }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{which}\NormalTok{(df\_list[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna}\SpecialCharTok{!=} \FunctionTok{lag}\NormalTok{(df\_list[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna))}
\NormalTok{      antenna          }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(df\_list[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{], df\_list[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna[changes])}
\NormalTok{      time             }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(df\_list[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{time[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{], df\_list[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{time[changes])}
\NormalTok{      id               }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(df\_list[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{id[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{], df\_list[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{id[changes])}
\NormalTok{      df\_list\_red[[i]] }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{data.frame}\NormalTok{(antenna, time, id)}
\NormalTok{    \}}

    
    \CommentTok{\# I bind the rows of the list (i.e. make it a dataframe, as it initially was)}
\NormalTok{    df2 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{bind\_rows}\NormalTok{(df\_list\_red)}
\NormalTok{    df2 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{as\_tibble}\NormalTok{(df2)}
    \CommentTok{\# df2 is basically the initial \textquotesingle{}new\_dataset\textquotesingle{} but the repeated reads}
    \CommentTok{\# have been eliminated only to keep the first one.}

    
    \CommentTok{\# I obtain the number of times each individual was read in two different antennas consecutively}
\NormalTok{    Changes }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{sapply}\NormalTok{(df\_list\_red, nrow)}
\NormalTok{    id }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{numeric}\NormalTok{() }\CommentTok{\# I obtain the individual names}
    \ControlFlowTok{for}\NormalTok{(i }\ControlFlowTok{in} \DecValTok{1}\SpecialCharTok{:}\FunctionTok{length}\NormalTok{(df\_list\_red))\{}
\NormalTok{      id[i] }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ df\_list\_red[[i]][}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{,}\DecValTok{3}\NormalTok{]\}}

    \CommentTok{\# I can generate a data frame with number of changes per individual}
\NormalTok{    df3 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{data.frame}\NormalTok{(id, Changes)}


\DocumentationTok{\#\# 2. DISTANCE TRAVELLED BY EACH INDIVIDUAL}

    \CommentTok{\# A for loop calculating the total distance travelled by each individuals between the antennas it\textquotesingle{}s been read at}
    
    \CommentTok{\# I define my Dist numerical vector}
\NormalTok{    Dist }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{numeric}\NormalTok{()}
    
    \ControlFlowTok{for}\NormalTok{ (i }\ControlFlowTok{in} \DecValTok{1}\SpecialCharTok{:}\FunctionTok{length}\NormalTok{(df\_list\_red))\{}
      \CommentTok{\# I make three numerical vectors, each for a distance type (i.e. width/length/diagonal)}
      \CommentTok{\# Each element of this vector is the number of times an individual achieved the pattern above}
      \CommentTok{\# E.g. width = c(4, 2, 3, 7) corresponds to an individuals crossing 4 times 11{-}\textgreater{}12, 2 times 12{-}\textgreater{}11,}
      \CommentTok{\# 3 times 13{-}\textgreater{}14 and 7 times 14{-}13.}
\NormalTok{      width }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{str\_count}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{paste}\NormalTok{(df\_list\_red[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna, }\AttributeTok{collapse=}\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{), seq.width)}
\NormalTok{      length }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{str\_count}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{paste}\NormalTok{(df\_list\_red[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna, }\AttributeTok{collapse=}\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{), seq.length)}
\NormalTok{      diagonal }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{str\_count}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{paste}\NormalTok{(df\_list\_red[[i]]}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna, }\AttributeTok{collapse=}\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{), seq.diag)}

      
      \CommentTok{\# I obtain the achieved distance per distance type (i.e. width/length/diagonal)}
\NormalTok{      dist.width }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{sum}\NormalTok{(width)}\SpecialCharTok{*}\NormalTok{pond.width}
\NormalTok{      dist.length }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{sum}\NormalTok{(length)}\SpecialCharTok{*}\NormalTok{pond.length}
\NormalTok{      dist.diagonal }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{sum}\NormalTok{(diagonal)}\SpecialCharTok{*}\NormalTok{pond.diagonal}
      
      \CommentTok{\# Total distance}
\NormalTok{      Dist[i] }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ (dist.width }\SpecialCharTok{+}\NormalTok{ dist.length }\SpecialCharTok{+}\NormalTok{ dist.diagonal)}
\NormalTok{    \} }\CommentTok{\# end of for loop}

    \CommentTok{\# Total distance travalled by all individuals}
\NormalTok{    df4 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{cbind}\NormalTok{(df3, Dist)}
    
    \FunctionTok{return}\NormalTok{(df4)}
\NormalTok{    \}}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

I run the function and obtain, for every individual, the distance it
travelled between all the antennas it's been read at. However, some
individuals might not have been read at all. Therefore, I add the
individuals that, potentially, haven't been read and indicate their
travelled distance as 0.

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{Travelled.distance }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{trav.dist}\NormalTok{(bottom\_clean\_df)}

\hypertarget{shoaling-index}{%
\subsection{6. Shoaling index}\label{shoaling-index}}

I write a function that computes the number of reads
(i.e.~\textasciitilde{} number of seconds, see \emph{clean.data}
function) each individuals spends accompanied, that is, read during the
same second at the same antenna in presence of at least one conspecific.

Input: A \emph{cleaned} data frame containing all the reads for one day.
Output: A data frame containing all the fish that have been read in
presence of a conspecific, and their corresponding: (i) number of
accompanied reads, (ii) total number of reads, (iii) proportion of the
time they spend in presence of a conspecific. The individuals that
haven't been read in presence of a conspecific are not in the data
frame.

\NormalTok{  clean\_df\_2 }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{split}\NormalTok{(clean\_df, }\AttributeTok{f =}\NormalTok{ clean\_df}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{antenna)}

      \CommentTok{\# I remove duplicated rows}
